## 5. Key Learning Concepts & Patterns

### 5.1 Advanced React Patterns

**State Management with Zustand:**
```jsx
// Store creation pattern
export const useStore = create((set, get) => ({
  state: initialValue,
  action: async (data) => {
    set({ loading: true });
    try {
      const result = await apiCall(data);
      set({ state: result, loading: false });
    } catch (error) {
      set({ error: error.message, loading: false });
    }
  }
}));
```

**Cross-Store Communication:**
```jsx
// Accessing other stores
const socket = useAuthStore.getState().socket;
socket.on("event", (data) => {
  set({ messages: [...get().messages, data] });
});
```

**Environment Configuration:**
```jsx
// Development vs Production
const BASE_URL = import.meta.env.MODE === "development" 
  ? "http://localhost:5001" 
  : "/";
```

### 5.2 Modern JavaScript Techniques

**Array Generation and Manipulation:**
```jsx
// Create array of specific length
const items = Array(6).fill(null);
const spread = [...Array(9)];

// Array methods
const filtered = items.filter(item => condition);
const mapped = items.map((item, index) => transform(item, index));
```

**String Manipulation:**
```jsx
// Capitalization
const capitalized = str.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + str.slice(1);

// Template literals with conditions
const className = `base-class ${condition ? "active" : "inactive"}`;
```

**Optional Chaining and Nullish Coalescing:**
```jsx
// Safe property access
const connected = socket?.connected;

// Default values
const theme = localStorage.getItem("theme") || "default";
```

### 5.3 Performance and UX Patterns

**Loading States:**
```jsx
// Granular loading states
const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);
const [isUpdating, setIsUpdating] = useState(false);

// Skeleton components
{isLoading ? <Skeleton /> : <Content />}
```

**Optimistic Updates:**
```jsx
// Update UI immediately, handle errors separately
set({ messages: [...messages, newMessage] });
try {
  await sendMessage(newMessage);
} catch (error) {
  // Revert or show error
}
```

**Event Cleanup:**
```jsx
// Socket event management
useEffect(() => {
  subscribeToMessages();
  return () => unsubscribeFromMessages();
}, [dependency]);
```

